data.title: Awards Gala
data.text:
Mary Kay Gutierrez named REALTOR® of the Year

On Friday, March 15th, GAAR held its Annual Awards Gala to honor member achievements for 2023. The evening was hosted by 2023 GAAR President, Carrie Traub and 2024 GAAR President, Morgan Cannaday at the Marriott Pyramid North.

More than 330 members celebrated the evening decked out in neon attire while enjoying dinner, beverages, music, and prizes!

Congratulations to our Awards Gala Winners!

2023 REALTOR® of the Year

One of the highest honors a member can receive during their real estate career, the REALTOR® of the Year Award acknowledges a member who has actively contributed to the success of both the REALTOR® organization and the industry, as well as exemplifies professionalism while serving the Greater Albuquerque community.

Mary Kay Gutierrez, Coldwell Banker Legacy

Doyle Pargin Lifetime Achievement Award

The Doyle Pargin Lifetime Achievement Award recognizes longevity and achievement in the profession, service to the industry, and model professionalism.

Mary Romero, Realty One Group Concierge

Salesperson of the Year

This award recognizes a member who achieved a notable level of production, volunteered at the Association, and exemplifies professionalism.

Jenn Cody Martin, Gold Key Realty

Rookie of the Year

This honor recognizes a new broker to the field who has had an outstanding first year in production.

Shawn Raitt, Coldwell Banker Legacy

Team Rookie of the Year

This honor recognizes a new broker to the field who has had an outstanding first year in production.

Nicole Sanchez, K2 Omni Group

GAAR Affiliate of the Year

This award recognizes a Blue Door Affiliate who has gone above and beyond to serve GAAR and it's members.

Lloyd Swartz, My Auction Addiction

GAAR Family Scholarship Recipients

This scholarship is awarded to family members who have just begun a career in real estate and are new members of GAAR and SWMLS.

Asel Venturi, Real Broker

Mandisa Routheni, Simply Real Estate

Special thanks to the GAAR & SWMLS Directors, Awards Gala Selection Committees, LEAP Committee, Sponsors, and GAAR Staff who made this neonic evening shine!
